}

comments.raw_text:
After further investigation, I confirmed that the All in One Sidebar (AiOS) extension broke the userChrome.css override suggested in Comment 2. After disabling that extension the above override worked with the menubar; however, not with the Addon-bar.

A more robust override is shown below in that it allows for both small and large icons to follow the Customize "Use Small Icons..." checkbox.

/*
 * Make menubar display icons according to the size selected by the
 * user in the customize toolbox
 */
#navigator-toolbox[iconsize="small"] #toolbar-menubar {
  counter-reset: smallicons;
}
#navigator-toolbox[iconsize="large"] #toolbar-menubar {
  counter-reset: largeicons;
}

